@john ezra 
Thank you John. My eyebrow also twitched at the idea that BLACKBOARDS are history. Not in schools round here they’re not. 
We lived in Hampshire for many years, further West than Dover but the same coast line.  Dig more than an inch or two down and you hit CHALK. Never needed to buy sticks of it, I just had a little pot of suitable sized chunks for use on the kitchen notice board.

@john ezra 

